    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `extensions/pulseboard/` — 7 New Files\n\nI explored the full codebase — `extensions/irc/`, `extensions/nostr/`, `extensions/telegram/`, and the core SDK — to understand every pattern. Here's what will be created:\n\n### Files to create\n\n| File | Key Detail |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `type: \"module\"`, full `openclaw` channel block |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, `channels: [\"pulseboard\"]`, minimal `configSchema` |\n| `src/types.ts` | 3 interfaces: `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `getPulseBoardRuntime`/`setPulseBoardRuntime` via `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `pulseBoardPlugin` via `createChatChannelPlugin()` with all required adapters |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry({ id: \"pulseboard\", ... })` |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### One key constraint discovered\n\n**`getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\")` would throw at runtime** — the function only works for channel IDs registered in `src/channels/ids.ts` (9 built-in channels; `pulseboard` is not one of them). Since we can't modify that file, `channel.ts` will **import** `getChatChannelMeta` as required (used as a type reference: `ReturnType<typeof getChatChannelMeta>`), then provide meta as a typed inline literal — exactly the same approach the Nostr plugin uses. Similarly, `sendText`'s return value needs a targeted cast since `\"pulseboard\"` is not yet a registered `DeliverableMessageChannel`.",
